Language Overview

Bengali Language Information

Speakers: 270 million Accents: West Bengal (Standard), Bangladeshi (Dhaka), Chittagonian, Sylheti Official language in: Bangladesh and India (West Bengal, Tripura, Assam) Spoken in: Bangladesh, eastern India (West Bengal, Tripura, Assam), and among Bengali diaspora An Indo-Aryan language with a distinctive script derived from Brahmi. Known for its melodious quality, rounded vowels, and rich literary tradition including Nobel laureate Rabindranath Tagore.
